Prion
diseases (for reviews, see Lasmezas
and Weiss, 2000<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">; Prusiner,
1998<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">; Weissmann and Aguzzi,
1997<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">) belong to a new class of fatal neurodegenerative disorders
affecting humans and animals. The key event in the development of the disease
is a conformational change in the cellular prion protein, PrPc.
